summary: Code generates a fake string of length 250000 by randomly choosing characters from the list 'p' using SystemRandom and prints it.

details.comment: Code generates a fake string of length 250000 by randomly choosing characters from the list 'p' using SystemRandom and prints it.
details.content:
# here we go, fake code.
p=[chr(x) for x in range(500)]
import random
k=""
for x in range(500*500):
    k+=random.SystemRandom().choice(p)
print(k)
